components.name: Wait for Daily Orders Partition
components.description: Checks the information_schema.partitions view until the daily partition for the orders table exists, then emits a success signal to unlock the ETL workflow.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this sensor starts the DAG.

components.name: Extract Incremental Orders
components.description: Reads new orders from the daily partition that matches the current date and outputs the raw dataset for downstream processing.

upstream_policy.description: Runs only after the partition sensor succeeds.

components.name: Transform Orders Data
components.description: Cleans, normalizes, and validates the extracted orders data (e.g., customer names, addresses, amounts, timestamps) before loading.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after successful extraction of incremental orders.

components.name: Load Orders to Data Warehouse
components.description: Writes the transformed orders data into the fact_orders table of the target data warehouse and updates related metrics.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful transformation of orders data.

connections.purpose: Write to fact_orders table in the warehouse

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

conn_id.description: Database connection identifier used by the sensor

timeout.description: Maximum wait time in seconds for the sensor

poke_interval.description: Interval in seconds between sensor checks

sources: Daily partition of the orders table in the source database (accessed via information_schema.partitions)
sinks: fact_orders table in the target data warehouse
intermediate_datasets: raw extracted orders data (output of extract_incremental)
